#1 Probably sigmoid cancer, questionable metastases
See History of Present Illness.  Discussed with Dr. Lehmann, who also met with Mrs. Martinez and her husband.  Please see his supervisory note.  Patient is scheduled for blood work, chest x-ray, ECG, CT colonography, PET scan, outside CT abdomen and pelvis March 25, 2010, reading.  We will get her outside tissue and tissue block for reading and IHC testing.  The patient is scheduled for Colon and Rectal Surgery, and depending on CT colonography and PET scan findings, patient may need to see Medical Oncology.  Whether or not she has metastases, she may very well need surgery to prevent obstruction.  Patient is OK anesthesia in my estimation with no cardiopulmonary issues.  She has no chest pain or shortness-of-breath and exercises frequently.
